##Experts respond that "new coronavirus has mutated" : Mutation sites 149, still stable

Linkage of three medical, bridge capital, direct health

The director-general of WHO said that the transmission of NCP was less efficient than influenza and did not appear to be driven by people who did not have the disease. This means that the outbreak it causes can be contained. But the recent global spread of the epidemic, people from all walks of life remain deeply concerned

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
By xinna Sun Aimin, CAIJING correspondent

Editor | Wang Xiao

As the new coronavirus began to emerge in more than 40 countries, it was increasingly being compared to another respiratory infection, dubbed Influenza.

"The transmission of NCP is less efficient than influenza, and transmission does not seem to be driven by people who do not have the disease. ". World Health Organization (WHO) director-general Tan Desai said during a media briefing on the new pneumonia outbreak on March 3,2020.

Although the new coronavirus is more effective than influenza in terms of transmission, the WHO believes that the latter is more efficient. The difference, Tandesai says, is that the main transmission drivers are different. In Influenza, the infected but not yet sick person is the main infectious person, but the transmission of new pneumonia is not so.

Evidence from China indicates that only 1 per cent of reported cases are asymptomatic, with the majority showing symptoms within 2 days. "We can quickly identify and stop the spread of new pneumonia on the first point, not as fast as the spread of influenza, " an epidemiologist told CAIJING.

As of 10:00 a.m. Central European time on March 3,10,566 cases of new coronary pneumonia (NCP) and 166 deaths had been confirmed in 72 countries outside China, according to the WHO. Eighty percent of the cases came from South Korea, Iran and Italy.

The WHO has raised the level of the new pneumonia outbreak from "high" to "very high" . This is the highest level of WHO Risk Assessment.

"The disease caused by the new coronavirus is more serious than influenza. We have vaccines and treatments for seasonal influenza, but there is no vaccine or specific treatment for COVID-19, " Tandser said.

WHO: transmission of new coronavirus less efficient than influenza

"The transmission efficiency of NCP is lower than that of influenza, " the WHO concluded after analysing the available data.

Both are respiratory disease, and the main mode of transmission is the same. Both are transmitted by droplets, which may come from the nose or mouth of the patient.

In the case of influenza, people who are infected but not yet sick are the main transmission drivers, but the new coronavirus does not seem to be, and its spread does not currently appear to be driven by people who are not sick, evidence from China indicates that only 1 per cent of reported cases are asymptomatic, with the majority showing symptoms within 2 days.

This is why no control measures for seasonal influenza have been discussed so far in the medical community, as contact tracing for seasonal influenza is not possible. But containment of NPV is possible, and contact tracing of npv to prevent infection is possible, so containment of human-to-human transmission of npv is achievable.

An epidemiologist analyzed a caijing reporter that the transmission of the disease in asymptomatic or newly diagnosed patients with pneumonia was not strong, although there were asymptomatic carriers and other conditions, but most transmission occurs in symptomatic patients. "We can quickly identify and stop the virus at the first point, so it doesn't spread as quickly as the flu does, " he said.

The proportion of truly asymptomatic cases is unclear but relatively rare, according to the china-who Joint Report on COVID-19 pneumonia (COVID-19) , published on the website of the NHRC on February 29, nor is it a major driver of transmission.

Although the transmission efficiency is not high, but based on existing studies, the transmission of new coronary pneumonia is significantly higher than influenza.

On January 29th a paper in the Journal The New England Journal of Medicine revealed the early spread of the new coronavirus. After analysing the first 425 confirmed cases in Wuhan, the researchers concluded that, on average, each new crown patient infected 2.2 people who did not have the disease.

At present, the magnitude of viral transmission is generally identified by a "basic reproductive number" (R0) , which is the expected number of new cases that will, on average, be transmitted by a case during the course of transmission. In general, epidemics increase whenever the number is greater than 1, and the goal of control measures is to reduce the number below 1.

But the authors of the paper said their estimate of the "basic regeneration number" of NCP was limited to the period before January 4.

According to the European Centre for Disease Control and Prevention (ECDC) , the R0 of the new coronavirus is about 2.2. This is comparable to the spread of the SARS virus, whose R0 is between 2 and 3. The ECDC's 2009 flu numbers are: R0 between 1.1 and 1.4.

In 2017 to 2018, the R0 of flu cases in China was 1.53, according to a paper by researchers including Chinese Academy of Engineering at IMD.

Although the viral genome was quickly deciphered and many papers published at home and abroad revealed the genomic characteristics, these characteristics could not explain the strong transmission of the new coronavirus.

On March 3rd, in a paper titled on the origin and continued evolution of SARS-COV-2, published in the Chinese Academy of Sciences, researchers analyzed genomic data from 103 new coronaviruses, there were a total of 149 mutation sites, and most of the mutations occurred recently.

Zhang Bao, associate director of the Southern Medical University's P3 laboratory, told Caijing that the more than 100 mutations suggested that the virus had not changed much and that it was relatively stable.

In addition, 101 of the 103 strains the researchers analyzed belonged to one of two subtypes. Specifically, the two subtypes differ in that the viral RNA genome is located at site 28144, where L is the t base (corresponding to Leucine, LEU) and s is the C base (corresponding to serine, Ser) .

Genomic data showed that l forms accounted for 70% and s forms 30% , and each l virus strain carried relatively more new mutations than s forms. At present, there is no evidence to explain the difference in transmission between the two subtypes.

Previously, NIH and University of Texas at Austin. Using freeze electron microscopy, McLellan's team found that the s protein of the new coronavirus and SARS virus had the same functional host cell Ace2, but the former had 10 -- 20 times higher extracellular domain attraction than SARS virus.

Zhang Bao's analysis, the ability of the virus to spread and death rate, more from the nature of the virus itself to find answers, including the virus's invasion, shelling, RNA transcription synthesis, protein translation assembly, virus maturity, release and many other aspects. Research in this area is not much, but China's scientific research in this area has made great progress in recent years, the next few months to six months will have results.

The mortality rate of NCP was higher than that of seasonal influenza

That's not the only difference between a new coronary pneumonia and a flu. "New crown pneumonia is more serious than seasonal influenza, " Tan said at the briefing, citing a second difference between the two.

There are two reasons why NCP is more serious. One is that no one is immune to NCP, and the other is the case fatality rate.

Although many people around the world are already immune to seasonal flu strains, the new coronavirus (COVID-19) is a new virus to which no one is immune, Tandsey explained. This means that more people are susceptible to infection, and some will develop serious diseases.

In his speech, Tan provided an update on the global epidemic: Globally, about 3.4 percent of new cases of pneumonia are reported to have died. By contrast, seasonal flu kills far less than 1% of those infected.

Previously, in the above-mentioned "china-world Health Organization Joint Investigation Report" , the crude case fatality rate in the early stage of the outbreak in China was relatively high, with 17.3% of cases occurring between January 1 and 10, and with the passage of time, the crude case fatality rate of cases after 1 February dropped to 0.7% . The joint mission noted that the level of medical services had changed as the epidemic progressed.

The majority of the patients were aged between 30 and 69 years, 77.8% of whom were at high risk of serious illness and death aged over 60 years. The latter clinical manifestations are dyspnea or exhaustion, low Oxygenation. The case fatality rate increased with age, the highest was over 80 years old (21.9%) . There was a significant increase in mortality among patients with complications, with cardiovascular disease accounting for 13.2% , followed by diabetes, hypertension, chronic respiratory disease, and cancer, the report said.

According to the available data, the case fatality rate of new pneumonia is lower than SARS and Mers, which are members of the same coronavirus family. According to WHO, the CFR for SARS is 15% , and the CFR for MERS is 34.4% .

Tamdesay believes that it is possible to contain the spread of new pneumonia compared to seasonal influenza. "We do not do contact tracing for seasonal influenza, but countries should do contact tracing for COVID-19 because it prevents infection and saves lives. "
